=John Makeham (1955-)=
===Keywords===
[[正名]] [[徐幹]]
==Publications==
===Monographs===
* Name and actuality in early Chinese thought. State University of New York, 1994
* Balanced Discourses: A Bilingual Edition. Yale University Press, 2002
* New Confucianism: A Critical Examination. New York: Palgrave Macmillan, 2003
* Transmitters and Creators: Chinese Commentators and Commentaries on the Analects. Cambridge, Mass: Harvard University Press, 2003
===Articles===
* The chien-pai Sophism: Alive and Well. Philosophy East and West, Volume 39, No. 1, 1989, pp. 75-81
* Names, Actualities, and the Emergence of Essentialist Theories of Naming in Classical Chinese Thought. Philosophy East and West, Volume 41, No. 3, 1991, pp. 341-363
* The Earliest Extant Commentary on Lunyu: Lunyu Zheng shi zhu. T'oung Pao, Volume 83, 1997, pp. 260-299
